                           <ab type="recto-verso">Source of description: Recto</ab>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <p>Written along the fibers in upright large-sized cursive letters with ligatures. The hand is practiced and adorned. Rho and iota are usually written with a tall leg prolonged to the following line. The scribe rotated between thin and thick letters by dipping his into his inkwell, especially before the signature. There is a dieresis attested on the signature. Verso is blank.</p>
